<L>__{interior garden city stage depot day}
<A>__{pan shot. rocklin enters and moves over to the counter, behind which is the stage agent, a mild looking man with pebble lens glasses. during the scene, the character who picked up the mail sacks from the platform, comes in, dumps the sacks on the counter and leaves.}
<C>__{stage agent}
<P>__{(to rocklin)}
<D>__{howdy.}
<C>__{rocklin}
<P>__{(indicating stage)}
<D>__{that the stage for santa inez?}
<C>__{stage agent}
<P>__{(nods)}
<D>__{leaving any minute.}
<A>__{rocklin puts his saddle on the counter, and taking out a wad of bills, drops them on the counter. the stage agent counts out the fare.}
<C>__{stage agent}
<D>__{santa inez seventeen fifty }
<P>__{(returning the balance)}
<D>__{name?}
<C>__{rocklin}
<D>__{rocklin.}
<A>__{the stage agent turns to make out the ticket. rocklin takes some tobacco and paper from his vest pocket as he glances outside.}
<C>__{rocklin}
<D>__{mind if i ride alongside the driver?}
<C>__{stage agent}
<P>__{(over his specs)}
<D>__{it's all right with me if it's all right with dave he's mad his last trip had a row with harolday, the boss old timer, dave an' a grumpy old cuss.}
<C>__{rocklin}
<P>__{(soberly)}
<D>__{i like grumpy old cusses hope to live long enough to be one.}
<C>__{stage agent}
<P>__{(puzzled)}
<D>__{yeah?}
<A>__{he shakes his head and hands rocklin the ticket, and moves over to the door with one of the mail sacks in his hand.}
